summary: I have all of these loops of thoughts in my head that are like, everyone's gonna judge you for doing this thing wrong, or you're...
caption:
I have all of these loops of thoughts in my head that are like, everyone’s gonna judge you for doing this thing wrong, or you’re not gonna say something funny or everyone’s gonna be looking at you. But I think going on tour has really helped me with that. Because now, I know if I had a family thing or I have to go somewhere i’m a lot less bothered. I think that’s because our audience is so nice.

happy birthday, @moonchair!

title: Happy Tuesday!
body:
So, my apartment complex offered me a trade up to a better apartment!  I’m going to look at it on Saturday and likely will take it.  

My car is clean, my apartment is clean…I feel like a new person!

My psychiatrist DID get my message and said he didn’t respond because didn’t have any suggestions for me. SO, I forgive him.

My side therapist helped me process a lot today.  I remembered being in first grade and having the teacher dump out my desk in front of everyone because it was messy. And we decided that was probably how my embarrassment and hoarding probably started.  It’s not the teacher’s fault, but that moment of being mortified and embarrassed instead of having her tell me / teach me how to clean or organize along with my already present social anxiety and OCD likely started this life long process.  

My side therapist is just the best.  When I told her how the teacher dumped out my desk in front of everyone like they do, she was like, “I’ve never heard of that before” and I was like…OH.  Really?  Wow.  Shaming me wasn’t really the best thing to do.

BUT anyway, the new pic of Phil was STUNNING wasn’t it?  OMG.  

And I miss Dan so much, but I want him to be happy so I will wait as long as I need to.  

My legs are aching still from the stress of last week.  It’s so weird. I feel like I have the flu, but I don’t.  Just lots of cortisol and adrenaline, I guess.  

I have a new student starting tomorrow. I’m excited and nervous (as always).  I love students, but the first few days are awkward for me with the social anxiety and also I so want them to feel comfortable and not nervous that I act a bit weird I think.  Then we settle into the routine and things go well. 

They finally approved by Saxenda medicine…BUT they said just because they approved it, it wouldn’t generate an order and I had to email them with the med, the doseage, and a bunch of other information.  WTH?  Caremark..more like, “We don’t care”-mark.  They aren’t very good at what they do.   Turns out, they approved it on the 26th of last month and if I hadn’t emailed, I’d never have known about it.  

Well, could I gripe anymore?? LOL. Things are good.  And how are you? How is your life going?  What are you reading right now?  Are you getting good rest?  Staying hydrated?  Looking forward to anything?  Doing any meditation?

I hope so.

Let me know how you are doing! :)

I’ll leave you with a little John Mulaney.   Good Night, sweet ones!
